README EN

* User guide
1. Log in into your instagram profile by browser
2. Navigate to a page with many followers, in order to use it as source (better a page with something in common with the profile you want to grow).
3. Open the followers list of the page (click on the followers number).
4. Open dev tools windows (press F12).
5. Navigate to the "Console" tab.
6. Paste the code you find in the the file "autoflw.js"
7. Press RETURN.
8. Write into the console the string "autoflw()" and press RETURN again.
9. Keep browser windows open until autofollower has to run.

The auto-follower will follow a person each 2 minutes (editable initializating the variable "numSecondiAttesa" with the numer of seconds),
in order to stay into instagram limits.
It will automatically skip people who you are already following or you sent request to.

Update 24/07/2019
* Auto-Unfollower
The behaviour is similar to the autofollower, the only difference is that you have to open your followed list.
There is, moreover, a variable called "idx", that numerically identifies the follower you want to start the autounfollow from
(the follower are chronologically sorted).
